<doc id="168479" wikidata="Q1156992" url="?curid=168479" title="Enhanced CD">
<text>Enhanced CD is a certification mark of the Recording Industry Association of America for various technologies that combine audio and computer data for use in both compact disc and CD-ROM players.

Formats that fall under the &quot;enhanced CD&quot; category include mixed mode CD (Yellow Book CD-ROM/Red Book CD-DA), CD-i, CD-i Ready, and CD-Extra/CD-Plus (Blue Book, also called simply Enhanced Music CD or E-CD).

==See also==
*DualDisc
*CDVU+
*Super Audio CD
*Mixed Mode CD

